The stratigraphical position of the plant-bearing bed at Rodalsberg may be seen from the Section given in text-fig. 1 (p. 4). It is considerably higher up in the series than the plant-bed at Munka Tagarp, but it lies probably a long dis- tance below the Cardimn-bed. The plant-bearing rock is a rust-coloured, fairly fine-grained sandstone, which occurs in close connection with a thin seam of poor coal.
